            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The Institución Libre de Enseñanza (Free Institute of Education) was founded in 1876 in Madrid by a group of university professors who wanted to provide education unrestricted by religious or political dogma (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9639.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Jiménez-Landi 1996</ref>, vol. 2). See also  <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11653A.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Hermenegildo Giner de los Ríos, 12 August 1878</ref>, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11766A.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Laureano Figuerola Ballester, 28 November 1878</ref>.</note>
            
